article.headline: Maine 69, Vermont 64
article.story: BURLINGTON, Vt. (AP) -- Kevin Reed scored 18 points and pulled down nine rebounds to lead Maine to a 69-64 win over Vermont in the America East on Thursday. The Black Bears (8-11, 3-4 America East) extend their winning streak to three games, while snapping Vermont's winning streak at seven games. The loss was the first for the Catamounts (12-6, 4-1) in league play. Vermont took a 62-56 lead after a 3-pointer by Colin McIntosh capped off a 7-0 run by the Catamounts with 3:27 left in the game. Reed then sunk consecutive 3-pointers for a 62-62 tie over the next 1:15. After a miss by Vermont, Junior Bernal drove to the lane and hit a short jumper to give Maine a two-point lead with 1:11 to go. Mike Trimboli tied the score with a jumper, but Reed banked a deep 3-pointer from the wing. Chris Bruff tacked on two late free throws for the final score.
